>My final answer doesn't make any sense to me.  I squared my 26 inch 
>diameter and got 676.  I multimplied that by pi (3.14) and got 
>2122.64 sq. inches and divided that by 1 foot/12 inches and got 
>176.89 feet per ball!  That can't be.  It's too big.  It's a 26 inch
>round ball, how can there be 176 feet of material required to cover 
>it?

A square foot is 12 inches by 12 inches, so it is 144 (12 times 12) 
SQUARE inches. You have to divide by 144, not 12, to convert to 
square feet.


